---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout title="Pediatric Sepsis" description="Simulation case for pediatric sepsis recognition and management.">
  <div class="breadcrumb">
    <a href={base}>Home</a>
    <span>›</span>
    <a href={`${base}cases/`}>Cases</a>
    <span>›</span>
    <span>Pediatric Sepsis</span>
  </div>

  <div class="case-header">
    <span class="card-tag">Pediatric</span>
    <h1>Pediatric Sepsis</h1>
    <div class="case-meta">
      <span>⏱ Duration: 45 minutes</span>
      <span>📊 Difficulty: Intermediate</span>
      <span>👥 Team Size: 3–4</span>
      <span>🏥 Setting: Pediatric ED</span>
    </div>
    <div class="tags" style="margin-top:1rem;">
      <span class="tag">Pediatrics</span>
      <span class="tag">Sepsis</span>
      <span class="tag">Critical Care</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="content-section">
    <h2>Case Overview</h2>
    <p>
      A 4-year-old male, Ethan Brooks, is brought to the Pediatric Emergency Department by his
      mother with a 2-day history of fever (up to 40°C), decreased oral intake, and increasing
      lethargy. On arrival he has mottled skin, is difficult to rouse, and is tachycardic.
    </p>
    <p>
      Learners must recognize pediatric septic shock using age-appropriate vital sign thresholds,
      initiate the Surviving Sepsis Campaign bundle, obtain appropriate cultures, and administer
      IV fluid boluses and antibiotics within the first hour of recognition.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="content-section">
    <h2>Patient Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Name:</strong> Ethan Brooks</li>
      <li><strong>Age:</strong> 4 years</li>
      <li><strong>Gender:</strong> Male</li>
      <li><strong>Weight:</strong> 16 kg</li>
      <li><strong>PMH:</strong> No prior medical history</li>
      <li><strong>Immunizations:</strong> Up to date</li>
      <li><strong>Allergies:</strong> NKDA</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="content-section">
    <h2>Initial Vital Signs</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>BP:</strong> 80/50 mmHg</li>
      <li><strong>HR:</strong> 172 bpm</li>
      <li><strong>RR:</strong> 38 breaths/min</li>
      <li><strong>SpO₂:</strong> 96% on room air</li>
      <li><strong>Temp:</strong> 39.8°C</li>
      <li><strong>Capillary Refill:</strong> 5 seconds</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="content-section">
    <h2>Learning Objectives</h2>
    <ul class="objective-list">
      <li>Recognize septic shock in a pediatric patient using age-appropriate vital sign criteria</li>
      <li>Apply the Surviving Sepsis Campaign Hour-1 Bundle in a pediatric patient</li>
      <li>Correctly calculate and administer IV fluid resuscitation (20 mL/kg NS bolus)</li>
      <li>Obtain blood cultures before antibiotic administration</li>
      <li>Select and administer appropriate broad-spectrum antibiotics empirically</li>
      <li>Communicate compassionately with a distressed parent during a pediatric emergency</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="content-section">
    <h2>Scenario Progression</h2>
    <h4>Phase 1 – Recognition (0–10 min)</h4>
    <p>
      Team receives handoff. Assessment reveals septic shock. IV access obtained; blood cultures,
      CBC, BMP, lactate ordered.
    </p>
    <h4>Phase 2 – Initial Resuscitation (10–30 min)</h4>
    <p>
      20 mL/kg NS bolus administered × 2. Broad-spectrum antibiotics (ceftriaxone) given.
      Lactate returns at 4.8 mmol/L. Fluid-refractory shock requiring vasopressors.
    </p>
    <h4>Phase 3 – Escalation &amp; ICU Transfer (30–45 min)</h4>
    <p>
      Norepinephrine initiated. PICU notified and transport arranged.
      Parent counseled on diagnosis and ICU admission.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="content-section">
    <h2>Debriefing Guide</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Were pediatric-specific vital sign thresholds used to recognize shock?</li>
      <li>Was the Hour-1 Bundle completed within the target timeframe?</li>
      <li>Were blood cultures obtained prior to antibiotics?</li>
      <li>How were fluid boluses dosed and reassessed?</li>
      <li>How did the team communicate with the patient's parent?</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div style="margin-top: 2rem;">
    <a href={`${base}cases/`} class="btn btn-primary" style="background: var(--color-primary); color: #fff;">← Back to Cases</a>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
